            "en":"Gear Ratio vs Teeth Ratio"
         },
         "description":{
            "en":"Let's see an example.<br/>We have a 20-teeth driver gear and a 60-teeth driven gear.<br/>Teeth Ratio is 20:60, or 1:3.<br/>Gear Ratio is 3:1.<br/>(It means that the 20-tooth-gear runs 3 rounds while the 60-tooth-gear makes 1 full circle.)"         
         },
         "challengeType":"horizontal"
      },
